ddiq |website=ESPNcricinfo |access-date=2019-08-15}}</ref>\n \nHe started his career as an all-rounder and in 1986/1987 WAPDA placed 3rd position in Quaid e Azam trophy under his captaincy. In 1992 Siddique was appointed as a head coach of WAPDA cricket team in Domestic circuit. His appointment at that time proved very vital for pakistan to win the 1992 cricket world cup.\n\n==Coaching career==\nAfter retiring from [[first-class cricket]] last in 1992, Siddique became the head coach of the [[Water and Power Development Authority cricket team]]<ref>[https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/20557504/salman-butt-mohammad-asif-get-wapda-contracts Butt and Asif get WAPDA contracts]</ref> side due to his service as captain. Siddique is a qualified [[Pakistan Cricket Board]] Level 1 and 2 coach. WAPDA won 1 [[Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]] and 2 National one day title and 5 times runner-up under his coaching in Pakistan domestic events.\n\n[[File:TeamWAPDAQAET2016Final.jpeg|frame|none|alt=Team WAPDA squad|Team WAPDA squad in Quaid e Azam trophy Final 2016-17 at National Stadium Karachi]]\n\n==Achievements as coach==\n'''[[Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]]''' \n* 2002/03 (Quarter-Final)\n* 2016/17 (Winner)\n*2017/18  (Runner Up)\n\n'''[[Patron's Trophy]]'''\n\n* 2006/07 (Quadrangular Stage)\n\n'''National One-day Championship'''\n* 1997/98 (Final Round)\n* 1998/99 (Final Round)\n* 1999/2000 (Semi-Final)\n* 2001/02 (Semi-Final)\n* 2002/03  (Runner-up)\n* 2004/05  (Winner)\n* 2005/06 (Semi-Final)\n* 2007/08 (Super Eight)\n* 2010/11 (Semi-Final)\n* 2014/15 (Winner)\n* 2016/17(Runner-Up)\n* 2017/18(Runner-Up)\n* 2018/19(Runner-Up)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cricinfo|ref=ci/content/player/39578.html}}\n*[https://www.pcb.com.pk/quaideazam-trophy-198687/match/3047.html Amjad Siddique Maidan first class century]\n*[https://www.pcb.com.pk/quaideazam-trophy-198687/points-table/268.html Points Table 1986/1987 Quaid e Azam Trophy https://www.pcb.com.pk/quaideazam-trophy-198687