layers/41/41688/41688.html |title=Amjad Saddiq |website=CricketArchive|url-access=subscription |access-date=2019-08-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/pakistan/content/player/39578.html |title=Amjad Saddiq |website=ESPNcricinfo |access-date=2019-08-15}}</ref>\n \nHe started his career as an all-rounder and in 1986/1987 WAPDA placed 3rd position in Quaid e Azam trophy under his captaincy. In 1992 Siddique was appointed as a head coach of WAPDA cricket team in Domestic circuit.\n\n==Coaching career==\nAfter retiring from [[first-class cricket]] last in 1992, Siddique became the head coach of the [[Water and Power Development Authority cricket team]]<ref>[https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/20557504/salman-butt-mohammad-asif-get-wapda-contracts Butt and Asif get WAPDA contracts]</ref> side due to his service as captain. Siddique is a qualified [[Pakistan Cricket Board]] Level 1 and 2 coach. WAPDA won 1 [[Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]] and 2 National one day title and 5 times runner-up under his coaching in Pakistan domestic events.\n\n[[File:TeamWAPDAQAET2016Final.jpeg|frame|none|alt=Team WAPDA squad|Team WAPDA squad in Quaid e Azam trophy Final 2016-17 at National Stadium Karachi]]\n\n==Achievements as coach==\n'''[[Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]]''' \n* 2002/03 (Quarter-Final)\n* 2016/17 (Winner)\n*2017/18  (Runner Up)\n\n'''[[Patron's Trophy]]'''\n\n* 2006/07 (Quadrangular Stage)\n\n'''National One-day Championship'''\n* 1997/98 (Final Round)\n* 1998/99 (Final Round)\n* 1999/2000 (Semi-Final)\n* 2001/02 (Semi-Final)\n* 2002/03  (Runner-up)\n* 2004/05  (Winner)\n* 2005/06 (Semi-Final)\n* 2007/08 (Super Eight)\n* 2010/11 (Semi-Final)\n* 2014/15 (Winner)\n* 2016/17(Runner-Up)\n* 2017/18(Runner-Up)\n* 2018/19(Runner-Up)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cricinfo|ref=ci/content/player/39578.html}}\n*[https://www.pcb.com.pk/quaideazam-trophy-198687/match/3047.html Amjad Siddique Maidan first class century]\n*[https://www.pcb.com.pk/quaideazam-trophy-198687/points-table/268.html Points Table 1986/1987 Quaid e Azam Trophy https://www.pcb.com.pk/quaideazam-trophy-198687/points-table/268.html]\n\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Water and Power Development Authority cricketers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani cricket coaches]]\n[[Category:Cricketers from Lahore]]\n[[Category:Pakistani cricketers]]\n", "name_user": "Soullover963852", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amjad_Siddique"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Saint Martin", "text_new": "{{about|2020 viral pandemic in French Saint Martin|epedemic in Dutch part of the island|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sint Maarten}}\n{{short description|Ongoing viral pandemic in French Saint Martin}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Martin\n| map1 = \n| places = \n| legend1 =\n| map2 =   \n| legend2 =\n| map3 =\n| legend3 =\n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]]\n| first_case = \n| arrival_date = 1 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=1|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = \n| confirmed_cases = 38<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/21042020%20st%20martin%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf|title=Bulletin n\u00b048 Information \u00ab coronavirus \u00bb Point de situation au 21 avril 2020|language=fr|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref> (2004-04-21)\n| suspected_cases =\n| recovery_cases = 19\n| deaths = 2\n| total_ili =\n| website = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the [[Overseas collectivity|French overseas collectivity]] of [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]] on 1 March 2020. The island is split in a Dutch and French part, with the airport on the Dutch side and the harbour on the French side. The first positive test was a French couple who made a stop-over in Saint Martin on route to [[collectivity of Saint Barth\u00e9lemy|Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] on 1 March 2020. They were screened and tested positive on the airport, but are counted on the French count.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.smn-news.com/st-maarten-st-martin-news/34052-state-of-affairs-on-st-maarten-regarding-the-covid-19.html |title=St. Martin News Network \u2013 State of Affairs on St. Maarten regarding the COVID-19. |website=smn-news.com|access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\nOn 1 March, a couple from the French part of [[Saint Martin]] island were diagnosed with [[COVID-19]]. Their son, who lives on the neighbouring island of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]], also tested positive.<ref name=\"first\">{{Cite web|url=http://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|title=Coronavirus : premiers cas confirm\u00e9s en Outre-mer, \u00e0 Saint-Martin et Saint-Barth|website=Polyn\u00e9sie la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302172416/https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, The collectivity's first death was recorded, after a 61-year-old died from breathing complications following a car accident. The patient tested positive for COVID-19 the following day.<ref name=\":33\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.loopnewsbarbados.com/content/saint-martin-records-first-coronavirus-death-3|title=Saint Martin records first coronavirus death|website=Loop News Barbados|language=en-EN|access-date=2020-03-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the second death was announced. It concerns a 80-year old man. <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n\nOn 19 April, Prime Minister [[Silveria Jacobs]] of Sint Maarten announced that the recent death was a Dutch citizen who was being treated on the French side. Last week he was flown to [[Guadelope]] for critical care, however as Dutch citizen he will be removed from the French Saint Martin count and added to the Dutch Sint Maarten count. <ref name=\"tenth_death\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/three-more-positive-cases-1-more-covid-19-death-for-st-maarten |title=Three more positive cases, 1 more COVID-19 death for St. Maarten|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=\"left\"\n|+\n'''Number of cases chronologically'''\n!Date\n!Cases\n!Recovered\n!Deaths\n|-\n|1 March\n|2 <ref name=\"first\"/>\n|0\n|0\n|-\n|15 March\n|2 <ref name=\"outremer\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/longs-formats-carte-coronavirus-combien-cas-outre-mer-807779.html|title=Coronovirus Nombre de cas confirm\u00e9s en Outre-mer|language=fr|website=Outre-mer la 1\u00e8re|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|17 March\n|3 <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|18 March\n|4 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/saint-martin/saint-martin-heure-du-confinement-814070.html|title=CORONAVIRUS : Saint-Martin, o\u00f9 2 patients sont hospitalis\u00e9s, \u00e0 l'heure du confinement.|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|21 March\n|4 <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|23 March\n|8 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-pres-650-cas-confirmes-recenses-region-caraibe-815150.html|title=Coronavirus : Pr\u00e8s de 650 cas confirm\u00e9s recens\u00e9s dans la grande r\u00e9gion Cara\u00efbe|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|25 March\n|11 <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|28 March\n|14 <ref>