aths}}</div>\n\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"> </div>\nSource: [https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-informations-et-recommandations-0 guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr]. No documents available before 17 April. Information prior to 17 April has been sourced with newspaper reports. For days without reports it is '''assumed''' in the graph that the numbers have remained the same.\n{{notelist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sint Maarten]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in the Collectivity of Saint Martin|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Caribbean|Saint Martin]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Overseas France|Saint Martin]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Collectivity of Saint Martin]]\n\n\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n{{SaintMartin-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{about|2020 viral pandemic in French Saint Martin|epedemic in Dutch part of the island|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sint Maarten}}\n{{short description|Ongoing viral pandemic in French Saint Martin}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Martin\n| map1 = \n| places = \n| legend1 =\n| map2 =   \n| legend2 =\n| map3 =\n| legend3 =\n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]]\n| first_case = \n| arrival_date = 1 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=1|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = \n| confirmed_cases = 38<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/21042020%20st%20martin%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf|title=Bulletin n\u00b048 Information \u00ab coronavirus \u00bb Point de situation au 21 avril 2020|language=fr|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref> (2004-04-21)\n| suspected_cases =\n| recovery_cases = 19\n| deaths = 2\n| total_ili =\n| website = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the [[Overseas collectivity|French overseas collectivity]] of [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]] on 1 March 2020. The island is split in a Dutch and French part, with the airport on the Dutch side and the harbour on the French side. The first positive test was a French couple who made a stop-over in Saint Martin on route to [[collectivity of Saint Barth\u00e9lemy|Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] on 1 March 2020. They were screened and tested positive on the airport, but are counted on the French count.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.smn-news.com/st-maarten-st-martin-news/34052-state-of-affairs-on-st-maarten-regarding-the-covid-19.html |title=St. Martin News Network \u2013 State of Affairs on St. Maarten regarding the COVID-19. |website=smn-news.com|access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\nOn 1 March, a couple from the French part of [[Saint Martin]] island were diagnosed with [[COVID-19]]. Their son, who lives on the neighbouring island of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]], also tested positive.<ref name=\"first\">{{Cite web|url=http://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|title=Coronavirus : premiers cas confirm\u00e9s en Outre-mer, \u00e0 Saint-Martin et Saint-Barth|website=Polyn\u00e9sie la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302172416/https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, The collectivity's first death was recorded, after a 61-year-old died from breathing complications following a car accident. The patient tested positive for COVID-19 the following day.<ref name=\":33\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.loopnewsbarbados.com/content/saint-martin-records-first-coronavirus-death-3|title=Saint Martin records first coronavirus death|website=Loop News Barbados|language=en-EN|access-date=2020-03-31|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the second death was announced. It concerns a 80-year old man. <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n\nOn 19 April, Prime Minister [[Silveria Jacobs]] of Sint Maarten announced that the recent death was a Dutch citizen who was being treated on the French side. Last week he was flown to [[Guadelope]] for critical care, however as Dutch citizen he will be removed from the French Saint Martin count and added to the Dutch Sint Maarten count. <ref name=\"tenth_death\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/three-more-positive-cases-1-more-covid-19-death-for-st-maarten |title=Three more positive cases, 1 more COVID-19 death for St. Maarten|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=\"left\"\n|+\n'''Number of cases chronologically'''\n!Date\n!Cases\n!Recovered\n!Deaths\n|-\n|1 March\n|2 <ref name=\"first\"/>\n|0\n|0\n|-\n|15 March\n|2 <ref name=\"outremer\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/longs-formats-carte-coronavirus-combien-cas-outre-mer-807779.html|title=Coronovirus Nombre de cas confirm\u00e9s en Outre-mer|language=fr|website=Outre-mer la 1\u00e8re|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|17 March\n|3 <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|18 March\n|4 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/saint-martin/saint-martin-heure-du-confinement-814070.html|title=CORONAVIRUS : Saint-Martin, o\u00f9 2 patients sont hospitalis\u00e9s, \u00e0 l'heure du confinement.|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|21 March\n|4 <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|23 March\n|8 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-pres-650-cas-confirmes-recenses-region-caraibe-815150.html|title=Coronavirus : Pr\u00e8s de 650 cas confirm\u00e9s recens\u00e9s dans la grande r\u00e9gion Cara\u00efbe|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|25 March\n|11 <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|28 March\n|14 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/deux-cas-supplementaires-covid-19-iles-du-nord-20-817302.html|title=Deux cas suppl\u00e9mentaires de Covid-19 dans les \u00eeles du Nord, 20 en tout.|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|29 March\n|15 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/st-martin-records-a-sharp-rise-in-covid-19-cases-and-first-death|title=St. Martin records a sharp rise in COVID-19 cases, and first death|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n|2\n|1\n|-\n|30 March\n|18 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-nouveau-deces-saint-martin-817952.html|title=Coronavirus : un nouveau d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Saint-Martin|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n|2\n|2\n|-\n|31 March\n|21 <ref name=\"news-03-31>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-21-cas-confirmes-saint-martin-3-plus-24-heures-818320.html|title=Coronavirus : 21 cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Saint-Martin, 3 de plus en 24 heures|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>\n|?\n|2\n|-\n|1 April\n|22 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https:/